Dialogue: 0,0:00:02.36,0:00:06.75,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Travel across the oceans of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.77,0:00:09.05,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Bellow a battle cry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.07,0:00:17.07,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Once your heart feels refreshed,\Nlet the signal to set sail ring out
Dialogue: 0,0:00:23.20,0:00:26.49,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,We've left the established course
Dialogue: 0,0:00:26.51,0:00:29.96,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Right now, we're rowing straight toward
Dialogue: 0,0:00:29.98,0:00:35.50,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,The borderline between\Nthe sky and the ocean
Dialogue: 0,0:00:35.52,0:00:41.72,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,In the dark depths of the ocean,\Nadventure holds its breath
Dialogue: 0,0:00:41.74,0:00:48.73,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you have a good\Ntime just imagining it?
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.75,0:00:53.06,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Travel across the oceans of the world
Dialogue: 0,0:00:53.08,0:00:55.32,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Bellow a battle cry
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.34,0:01:03.34,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Once your heart feels refreshed,\Nlet the signal to set sail ring out
Dialogue: 0,0:01:09.49,0:01:12.96,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,"That feeling" I get when embarking
Dialogue: 0,0:01:12.98,0:01:16.21,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Is something I hope to remember always
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.23,0:01:22.07,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,If I can, I won't be afraid of anything
Dialogue: 0,0:01:22.09,0:01:27.97,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,With our pulses racing,\Nlet's go on a trip now
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.99,0:01:35.02,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Shy hearts engrave\Nthe rhythm of adventure
Dialogue: 0,0:01:35.04,0:01:39.51,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Snatch up the treasure here and there
Dialogue: 0,0:01:39.53,0:01:41.72,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,While laughing out loud
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.74,0:01:46.06,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,As we dash by like a noisy party
Dialogue: 0,0:01:46.08,0:01:49.04,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Make some waves...
Dialogue: 0,0:01:49.06,0:01:50.85,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Life is "Adventurous"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:50.87,0:01:52.60,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Be aware it's "Dangerous"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.62,0:01:54.17,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Who's gonna be "One of us"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:54.19,0:01:55.83,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,And a trip goes on because
Dialogue: 0,0:01:55.85,0:01:57.45,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,We da pirate of the "Mass"
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.47,0:01:58.96,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,To the West, To the East
Dialogue: 0,0:01:58.98,0:02:00.62,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Gotta find my way, Sail away
Dialogue: 0,0:02:00.64,0:02:01.69,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,All the way to "One piece"!!
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.71,0:02:05.89,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Stuff a dream into your empty chest
Dialogue: 0,0:02:05.91,0:02:08.18,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,And spread your wings
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.20,0:02:12.63,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,If the wind blowing through\Nthem dyes your heart
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.65,0:02:14.98,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Let's press forward
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.00,0:02:19.17,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Snatch up the treasure here and there
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.19,0:02:21.52,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,While laughing out loud
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.54,0:02:25.78,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,As we dash by like a noisy party
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.80,0:02:33.80,Italics,song,0000,0000,0000,,Make some waves...
Dialogue: 0,0:02:33.94,0:02:37.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The time is the Great Pirate Era.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.02,0:02:41.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Countless pirates fight \Ndesperately for the One Piece,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.02,0:02:45.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the great treasure left behind by \NGold Roger, King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:45.86,0:02:48.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Monkey D. Luffy, \Na boy whose body turned to rubber
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.77,0:02:50.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after he ate the Gum-Gum Fruit,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.69,0:02:53.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,also takes to the sea to become\N the next King of the Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.57,0:02:57.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As Luffy and his friends \Novercome numerous adventures,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:57.60,0:03:03.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the World Government is less and\N less able to ignore their existence.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.50,0:03:05.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is exciting!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:05.90,0:03:09.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of adventure \Nis waiting for us next?!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:09.19,0:03:12.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The crew, on its way to the New World,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:12.34,0:03:20.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will speed along the Grand Line again today!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.09,0:03:23.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy was ejected from \Nthe Sabaody Archipelago
Dialogue: 0,0:03:23.18,0:03:25.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,by Bartholomew Kuma, a Warlord of the Sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.01,0:03:27.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Separated from his friends,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:27.41,0:03:32.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he arrived alone at the female-only \Nempire of Amazon Lily!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:32.48,0:03:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Captured by the Pirate Empress Hancock,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:35.31,0:03:37.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Luffy battled in mortal combat \Nwith her younger sisters,
Dialogue: 0,0:03:37.88,0:03:41.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sandersonia and Marigold who had \Neaten the Snake-Snake Fruit.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:41.69,0:03:43.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How rude!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:43.43,0:03:46.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mari! Get him now!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:46.06,0:03:49.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't, Sister Sonia.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:49.36,0:03:53.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are now... being protected...
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.13,0:03:55.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...by that man!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:55.03,0:04:03.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that you'd rather die\N than show it to someone.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:08.76,0:04:16.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Hancock's Confession \NThe Sister's Abhorrent Past"
Dialogue: 0,0:04:43.39,0:04:48.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it okay, now?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:48.35,0:04:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Sonia!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:56.06,0:04:57.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're sorry, Big Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.73,0:05:02.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We're sorry that we lost and \Nhad to be saved by our enemy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.18,0:05:10.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you up next?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:13.06,0:05:17.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's enough.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.07,0:05:19.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel like it.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:19.18,0:05:20.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, yeah?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:20.75,0:05:25.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I hope that she's not damaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:25.06,0:05:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Alright then,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:26.28,0:05:31.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,these people you turned to stone; \Nturn them back.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:31.74,0:05:33.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:33.28,0:05:36.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can do something, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.46,0:05:39.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They were just trying to defend me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.11,0:05:40.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They didn't do anything wrong!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:40.62,0:05:46.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, please?!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.57,0:05:47.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, indeed,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:47.75,0:05:52.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can revert them if I want.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.07,0:05:54.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.53,0:05:58.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You said that you want \Nto go someplace by ship.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:58.37,0:06:01.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, my crew's waiting for me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:01.25,0:06:02.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, that's nice.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:02.98,0:06:05.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But I can only make \None of your wishes come true.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.33,0:06:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's either revert them
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.57,0:06:10.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,or help you to get off this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.62,0:06:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Choose one wish and give up on the other!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:16.87,0:06:21.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Snake Princess. You are so...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.34,0:06:24.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can't fool me.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.29,0:06:27.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Reveal your true nature, Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.34,0:06:30.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's great! Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.52,0:06:36.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That means you're going to help them, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:36.29,0:06:44.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you... very much!!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:46.58,0:06:48.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He doesn't hesitate at all.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:48.55,0:06:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How is it that a man who has such great Haki
Dialogue: 0,0:06:51.22,0:06:55.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,bows his head in order \Nto save his benefactors...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.06,0:06:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Maybe, he is...
Dialogue: 0,0:06:57.69,0:07:05.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Sis...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:26.29,0:07:28.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Anyway, that man...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:28.53,0:07:32.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can't believe he defeated the sisters.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.21,0:07:34.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, but...
Dialogue: 0,0:07:34.44,0:07:36.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't think Snake Princess will forgive him
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.64,0:07:39.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after he was so rude to her
Dialogue: 0,0:07:39.43,0:07:47.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,nor will she forgive the people \Nwho let him in to this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.76,0:07:48.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margaret!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.85,0:07:50.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sweetpea!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.12,0:07:51.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Aphelandra!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:51.48,0:07:53.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, here you all are!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:53.46,0:07:56.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great! She turned you back from stone!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.86,0:08:01.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was so worried because you \Nsuddenly started to vouch for him.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:01.08,0:08:02.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She's right.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:02.43,0:08:05.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was afraid of what would happen to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:05.28,0:08:08.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Turned us back?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:08.02,0:08:09.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to us?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:10.00,0:08:13.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have absolutely no recollection.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.40,0:08:14.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't you remember?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:14.73,0:08:15.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No I don't...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:15.77,0:08:19.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The next thing I knew, that man\N was there and he was really happy.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.67,0:08:21.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I'm so relieved!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:21.86,0:08:26.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was worried that you were going to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:26.11,0:08:27.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No one's here...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:27.58,0:08:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it all finished now?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:29.43,0:08:33.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.16,0:08:36.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Snake Princess!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:36.16,0:08:38.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um...
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.40,0:08:46.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Keep dedicating yourself to \Nyour duty to protect our country.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:50.22,0:08:52.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...And that was it.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:52.58,0:08:53.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Great!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.01,0:08:55.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When you're turned to stone,
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.36,0:08:57.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it's hard to remember what \Nhappened before and after.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:57.69,0:08:59.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'll tell you what happened.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.00,0:09:01.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margaret.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:01.47,0:09:03.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What happened to the man?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.51,0:09:04.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What about Snake Princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:04.93,0:09:08.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did she turn him to stone this time?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.86,0:09:11.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know that much,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:11.26,0:09:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but it seems like he got\N summoned to the Kuja Castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:13.21,0:09:17.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:17.67,0:09:20.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, I want to know! \NWhat do you want from me?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:20.26,0:09:21.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.11,0:09:25.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is there a meal after the battle?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:25.86,0:09:28.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If that's what it is, I'll be happy!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:28.74,0:09:31.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What kind of food is popular here?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:31.22,0:09:33.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet it's some kind of meat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:33.05,0:09:35.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I should be thanking you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:35.81,0:09:36.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:36.89,0:09:38.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, please!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:38.50,0:09:40.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Thank you" isn't something I can eat!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.34,0:09:42.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If anybody had seen what's on our backs,
Dialogue: 0,0:09:42.58,0:09:46.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,there is no way that we \Ncould stay in this country.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:46.90,0:09:49.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You may come in.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:49.74,0:09:51.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Come inside, Man.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:51.67,0:09:52.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:52.99,0:09:54.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Inside of the curtain.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:54.54,0:09:57.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, is that where the food is?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:57.20,0:09:58.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm coming...
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.68,0:10:00.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, we're not eating.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.91,0:10:04.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, what are you doing \Nwith your clothes off?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:04.05,0:10:07.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As always, you are reacting rudely.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:07.92,0:10:15.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But that's okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:26.26,0:10:28.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is the mark...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:28.70,0:10:32.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...that you said...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:32.55,0:10:35.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...you had seen somewhere.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:35.67,0:10:40.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Take a good look at it, again.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:40.81,0:10:42.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you see this?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.47,0:10:50.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you know the meaning of this mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.46,0:10:56.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Answer me, now!
Dialogue: 0,0:10:56.51,0:11:04.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's not something I want to show people.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.60,0:11:09.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As I suspected, it's a bit different \Nfrom what I've seen before.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.32,0:11:13.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have a friend called Hachi \Nwho is a fish-man...
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.43,0:11:14.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A fish-man?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:14.35,0:11:16.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:16.11,0:11:17.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And he has a similar mark on his forehead
Dialogue: 0,0:11:17.88,0:11:19.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,so I thought it was the same.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.63,0:11:21.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't know anything about your mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.55,0:11:24.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If he doesn't know, why don't you tell him?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:24.42,0:11:25.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Granny Nyon!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.57,0:11:26.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you come in from?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.76,0:11:28.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Be honest, Snake Princess.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:28.96,0:11:35.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You have seen clearly\N how tolerant that man is.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:35.63,0:11:37.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't be afraid.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:37.06,0:11:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tell him everything that you want to share.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.93,0:11:43.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:43.94,0:11:47.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a pirate,\N Monkey D. Luffy, am I right?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:47.58,0:11:49.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.03,0:11:51.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How do you know about me?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:51.29,0:11:53.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,How can you be so casual
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.10,0:11:56.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,after you caused such\N a sensation in the world?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:56.23,0:12:00.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look at this newspaper! \NJust days ago, this man...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.53,0:12:04.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...at Sabaody Archipelago \Nnear the center sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:04.21,0:12:06.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,caused a horrific and grave incident
Dialogue: 0,0:12:06.69,0:12:14.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,when he dealt a blow to a Celestial Dragon!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.90,0:12:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Dealt a blow to a Celestial Dragon?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.07,0:12:23.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It is a miracle that he was able to get away
Dialogue: 0,0:12:23.05,0:12:28.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the supreme powers\N at the center sea after that.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:28.04,0:12:30.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And in only a couple days,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:30.85,0:12:34.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he arrived here so far away.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.76,0:12:37.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's all beyond our understanding.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.85,0:12:40.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Who are you?!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.52,0:12:41.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I told you!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:41.87,0:12:43.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was blown away suddenly.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:43.83,0:12:47.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have no idea where this place is!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.81,0:12:48.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, and another thing -
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.90,0:12:52.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't feel sorry for that Celestial Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.62,0:12:53.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That bastard!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.58,0:12:56.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess what he did to my friend?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.88,0:12:59.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-Then...
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.50,0:13:06.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it is true that you punched \Na Celestial Dragon.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.61,0:13:08.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,T-There are still...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.71,0:13:16.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...foolish people like that...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:16.72,0:13:24.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...in this world?!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.21,0:13:30.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The ones who put their lives at risk \Nto challenge those celestials...
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.76,0:13:38.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...like him!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:38.48,0:13:46.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:58.99,0:14:02.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will tell you everything
Dialogue: 0,0:14:02.16,0:14:04.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,including the meaning of the symbol
Dialogue: 0,0:14:04.14,0:14:07.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that your fish-man friend \Nhas on his forehead.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.53,0:14:11.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hachi's mark?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:11.45,0:14:15.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:15.70,0:14:19.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"The Claw of the Celestial Dragon."
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.27,0:14:27.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It's an emblem of the Celestial Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.12,0:14:34.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,People who were fed by \Nthe World Nobles all get...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.29,0:14:38.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...this permanent brand to \Nshow that you are subhuman!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:38.32,0:14:42.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Celestial Dragons?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.63,0:14:46.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The three of us were...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.05,0:14:54.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...once...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.14,0:15:03.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...slaves of World Nobles!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.73,0:15:21.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You were... slaves?!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.49,0:15:32.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It happened when I was 12...
Dialogue: 0,0:15:32.49,0:15:34.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Starboard, all clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:35.00,0:15:37.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Port, all clear, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.44,0:15:39.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Bow, all clear.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.84,0:15:42.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,High visibility, all serene!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:42.46,0:15:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't fall into the sea!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.19,0:15:48.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don't make fun of me!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:48.02,0:15:50.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I've become a warrior!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.11,0:15:51.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:51.27,0:15:54.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We trust you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.56,0:15:56.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That's our Big Sis!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:56.06,0:15:58.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We'll support you!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:58.36,0:16:02.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I bet you're hungry! I brought a snack!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.37,0:16:03.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hancock?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.58,0:16:06.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sonia! Mari! Where are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.17,0:16:13.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Three of us were taken \Nfrom the Kuja pirate ship...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.20,0:16:19.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...and we were sold!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.15,0:16:20.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,From that point,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.96,0:16:28.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,all we have are terrible memories \Nthat we don't even want to remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.67,0:16:42.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We saw men for the first time
Dialogue: 0,0:16:42.84,0:16:48.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and they were nothing but figures of horror.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.26,0:16:50.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sister Sonia, calm down!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.99,0:16:53.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The memory haunts us.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:53.59,0:16:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,W-Wow! H-Hey! That's enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:55.70,0:16:58.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No need to force the memories! \NYou don't have to tell me!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.33,0:16:59.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was awful.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.94,0:17:02.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There was no hope.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:02.13,0:17:04.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We kept thinking about death!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.59,0:17:07.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey! You...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.62,0:17:09.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But...
Dialogue: 0,0:17:09.30,0:17:11.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...one night four years later,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.98,0:17:16.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,something happened that made \Nthe World Government tremble.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:16.87,0:17:19.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Nobody will challenge \Nthe Celestial Dragons."
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.59,0:17:22.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That was the cardinal rule in their world.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.24,0:17:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there was a man who climbed \Nthe Red Line with his bare hands
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.22,0:17:34.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and slipped into the Celestial \NDragons' Holyland of Marejois.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:37.87,0:17:41.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was an adventurer who\N later led the Fish-Man Pirates,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.16,0:17:44.34,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,named Fisher Tiger.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:44.36,0:17:46.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In order to free all the slaves
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.34,0:17:48.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,from the town there his fellow\N fish-men were being tortured,
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.86,0:17:52.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he fought with all his might.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.53,0:17:54.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We are free! We are free!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.00,0:17:58.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He disliked humans as a species
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.24,0:18:00.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but he was being fair to all slaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.19,0:18:05.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and let thousands of slaves \Nof different species go free.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.19,0:18:13.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We prepared to die and ran among the others.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.86,0:18:30.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We owe him an immeasurable debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.31,0:18:35.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tiger released many fish-men to the sea,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.74,0:18:40.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,but ones who were slaves had \Na mark that cannot be erased.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.31,0:18:43.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tiger has made the World Government his enemy
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.38,0:18:46.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he formed the \NSun Pirates with former slaves
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.99,0:18:51.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and sailed out into the open sea.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:51.78,0:18:54.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As though breaking a curse,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:54.38,0:19:02.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he changed the Celestial Dragon's \Nemblem on everyone's bodies...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.12,0:19:05.63,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...into the symbol of the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:05.65,0:19:10.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you thought was similar \Nto the mark on my back is
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.42,0:19:13.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the sun symbol of the Sun Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.85,0:19:15.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yeah, you're right.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.54,0:19:19.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The one Hachi has on his \Nforehead looks like the sun.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.58,0:19:22.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Does that mean he was a slave, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:22.59,0:19:25.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It doesn't necessarily mean that he was.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:25.49,0:19:29.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The mark is made in such a way \Nthat it is impossible to tell...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.19,0:19:32.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...whether they are former slaves or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.46,0:19:37.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm pretty sure that he once was \Na member of the Sun Pirates.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:37.83,0:19:41.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,In fact, Fisher Tiger is already dead and...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:41.41,0:19:48.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...the Sun Pirates have split \Nup into several groups.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:48.93,0:19:52.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, when did you get hurt there?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.22,0:19:55.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, this? Don't worry about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:55.99,0:19:59.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He has a complicated past, too...
Dialogue: 0,0:19:59.02,0:20:01.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So this is the reason \Nthat the mark on our backs
Dialogue: 0,0:20:01.88,0:20:04.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,is similar to the fish-men's mark.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:04.50,0:20:07.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Okay, I pretty much understand.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.57,0:20:11.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Surprisingly, when we were slaves,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:11.07,0:20:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we were forced to eat Love-Love Fruit
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.87,0:20:16.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Snake-Snake Fruit\N for their entertainment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.41,0:20:18.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and that enabled us to deceive our nation
Dialogue: 0,0:20:18.16,0:20:22.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and preserve the secret.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.15,0:20:27.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If you didn't cover up \NSonia's back at that moment,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:27.24,0:20:34.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would have been impossible \Nfor us to stay on this island.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:34.85,0:20:42.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don't want to let anyone \Nknow about our past!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.06,0:20:52.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I won't stop at deceiving \Nour whole nation to hide it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.23,0:20:56.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We won't open ourselves up at any price!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.94,0:21:02.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don't want anybody to \Ntake advantage of us again!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.01,0:21:06.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm scared of being caught off guard.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.05,0:21:12.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It terrifies me. I can't take it!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.44,0:21:16.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Big Sis...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:16.75,0:21:17.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ho!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:17.66,0:21:19.95,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But this is the first time in a long time
Dialogue: 0,0:21:19.97,0:21:23.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,that you've shown your emotions like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.66,0:21:26.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Recently, I've thought \Nthat the Snake Princess
Dialogue: 0,0:21:26.46,0:21:31.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,must have turned to ice or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:31.59,0:21:32.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.68,0:21:34.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You are a traitor who \Nleft the country behind!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.88,0:21:36.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You shut up!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.01,0:21:39.00,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You three were miserable
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.02,0:21:42.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and didn't know how to \Nreturn to this island...
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.55,0:21:46.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...after you ran away from \Nthe Celestial Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:46.56,0:21:51.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Who brought you back?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:51.22,0:21:56.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should be thankful that \NI was living outside of this country!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:56.37,0:21:58.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What you are talking about was a small favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:58.56,0:21:59.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What did you say?!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:59.63,0:22:00.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Granny Nyon...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.64,0:22:05.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I always keep an eye on \Nyou three as a mother would!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.98,0:22:09.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And you call it "small \Nfavor", Snake Princess?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.85,0:22:15.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, get your hands off of me! Mari! Sonia!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:15.20,0:22:17.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you going to...
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.52,0:22:21.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,...look down on me; a former slave?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.01,0:22:30.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:32.16,0:22:34.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.55,0:22:42.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Like I told you - I hate \Nthe Celestial Dragons!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:44.86,0:22:46.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I like you!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:46.84,0:22:49.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Didn't you say that you had one more wish?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.76,0:22:50.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:50.74,0:22:53.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where do you want to go?\N I'll give you a ride!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.32,0:23:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,For real?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.46,0:23:09.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Kuja Pirates hold a banquet.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:09.18,0:23:11.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,When Luffy is mobbed by curious women,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:11.68,0:23:14.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Margaret saves him and takes \Nhim to Granny Nyon's house.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.70,0:23:18.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But there, Luffy finds out that \Nhis brother Ace is in trouble,
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.35,0:23:21.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and he's forced to make a big decision.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.07,0:23:22.56,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,On the next episode of One Piece!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.58,0:23:26.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,"Saving Ace!\N The Next Stop: the Great Prison!"
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.28,0:23:34.28,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I'm gonna be King of the Pirates!!
